<help-screen version="1">
    <thumbnail>
        <script>
            <block s="reportNewCostumeStretched">
                <l/>
                <l/>
                <l/>
            </block>
        </script>
    </thumbnail>
    <header>Stretch a costume.</header>
    <box color="gray">
        <column>
            <diagram>
                <script>
                    <block s="reportNewCostumeStretched" bubble="1">
                        <l>alonzo</l>
                        <l>100</l>
                        <l>50</l>
                    </block>
                </script>
                <bubbles>
                    <img src="reportNewCostumeStretched_alonzo1.png" width="48" height="40"/>
                </bubbles>
            </diagram>
            <diagram>
                <script>
                    <block s="reportNewCostumeStretched" bubble="1">
                        <l>alonzo</l>
                        <l>50</l>
                        <l>100</l>
                    </block>
                </script>
                <bubbles>
                    <img src="reportNewCostumeStretched_alonzo2.png" width="48" height="40"/>
                </bubbles>
            </diagram>
            <p>
                Note that this is a reporter, not a command! It reports the
                stretched costume. If you want the sprite to wear it, you have to say
            </p>
            <script>
                <block s="doSwitchToCostume">
                    <block s="reportNewCostumeStretched">
                        <l>alonzo</l>
                        <l>50</l>
                        <l>100</l>
                    </block>
                </block>
            </script>
        </column>
    </box>
    <box color="blue">
        <column>
            <p>
                Note: If the first input is a list of pixels rather than a
                costume, then the x and y inputs are interpreted not as a
                percent (of the costume's original dimensions) but as an
                absolute number of pixels, so you can do this:
            </p>
            <script>
                <block s="doSwitchToCostume">
                    <block s="reportNewCostumeStretched">
                        <block s="reportMap">
                            <block s="reifyReporter">
                                <autolambda>
                                    <block s="reportIfElse">
                                        <block s="reportGreaterThan">
                                            <block s="reportListItem">
                                                <l>4</l>
                                                <l/>
                                            </block>
                                            <l>0</l>
                                        </block>
                                        <block s="reportCONS">
                                            <l>255</l>
                                            <block s="reportCDR">
                                                <l/>
                                            </block>
                                        </block>
                                        <l/>
                                    </block>
                                </autolambda>
                                <list/>
                            </block>
                            <block s="reportGetImageAttribute">
                                <l><option>pixels</option></l>
                                <block s="reportPenTrailsAsCostume"/>
                            </block>
                        </block>
                        <block s="reportGetImageAttribute">
                            <l><option>width</option></l>
                            <block s="reportPenTrailsAsCostume"/>
                        </block>
                        <block s="reportGetImageAttribute">
                            <l><option>height</option></l>
                            <block s="reportPenTrailsAsCostume"/>
                        </block>
                    </block>
                </block>
            </script>
            <p>
                <text>1. Find</text>
                <script>
                    <block s="reportGetImageAttribute">
                        <l><option>pixels</option></l>
                        <l>some costume</l>
                    </block>
                </script>
            </p>
            <p>
                <text>2. Transform the pixels using</text>
                <text font="Courier" color="red">map</text>
            </p>
            <p>
                <text>3. Use</text>
                <text font="Courier" color="purple">stretch</text>
                <text>to restore the width and height</text>
            </p>
        </column>
    </box>
</help-screen>
